Half, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(half, peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #colander{}.

In a large #saucepan{}, heat a splash of @oil{a splash} over high heat. Once hot add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and fry, turning occasionally, until golden brown all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside. Preheat your #grill{} to high heat.

In the now empty saucepan, heat another little splash of @oil{a splash} over medium heat and a knob of @?butter{knob} (if you have it!) over medium heat. Pop in the onion and cook until soft and starting to colour, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir half the garlic, the @dried Italian herbs{1}(mixed), @tomato puree{30%g}, @chorizo{60%g}(sliced) and @sugar{1/4}(pinch) into the pan. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Mix in half of the beans, the @water{300%ml} and the @chicken stock powder{1/2}. Bring to the boil, stir to dissolve the stock, then reduce the heat to medium. Simmer for ~{5%minutes}. Mash the other half of the beans, then stir into the stew. > This will help thicken the stew. Pop the chicken back into the pan and simmer gently until the chicken is cooked through, ~{5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle!

While the chicken is cooking, mix the rest of the garlic, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} together in a #small bowl{}. Slice the @ciabatta{1}(sliced in half lengthways) in half lengthways (as if you were making a sandwich!) and drizzle the garlic oil over the cut side. Pop onto a #baking tray{} and place under the grill until nicely toasted, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Just before you serve, stir in the @baby spinach{125%g} one handful at a time. Cook until just wilted, ~{2%minutes}. Chop the ciabatta into wide chunks. Serve your stew in deep #bowls{} with the garlic bread on the side. Enjoy!